      "role": "user",
      "content": "oh wow, that's a a pretty strong take. you're saying it's basically a flawed strategy? i was looking for a more academic overview of the different schools of thought, like the supply-side arguments about capital investment and how they view these cuts. can you explain why those arguments might be considered wrong or ineffective in this context?",
